[55.790271, "o", " is tiny (well under 50K). Per Hard Rule C I shouldn't over-chunk, but the user explicitly wants \u001b[0m\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mthe chunk→map→reduce playbook with batched query$llm. I'll honor it lightly: one map prompt per file \u001b[0m\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(4 prompts in one batched call), asking for structured JSON classification, then reduce in a clojure \u001b[0m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mfence. First I need to see the actual ERROR line contents to confirm and to feed the map step.\u001b[0m\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mbash\u001b[0m({\"command\" \"for f in logs/web-01.log logs/web-02.log logs...): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 22ms, 1.3k chars\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(30483 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(19.2s)\u001b[0m\u001b[26;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mI have all 16 ERROR lines from prior iterations. Data is tiny (1169 bytes, 4 files). User explicitly \u001b[0m\u001b[27;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mwants the chunk→map→reduce playbook with batched query$llm, so I'll honor it: one map prompt per \u001b[0m\u001b[28;1H\u001b[2"]
[55.790296, "o", "K         \u001b[2mfile (4 prompts, one batch), asking for one-line JSON per ERROR line with a category, then reduce \u001b[0m\u001b[29;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mwith rlm$parse-map-results + rlm$reduce-counts in a clojure fence. query$llm is synchronous in the \u001b[0m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2msandbox so I can map then reduce in one block.\u001b[0m\u001b[31;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;93m⠇\u001b[0m\u001b[2m]\u001b[0m \u001b[96mReasoning...\u001b[0m\u001b[2m (45.8s)\u001b[0m"]
