[106.644733, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[1m\u001b[96mBrainyard TUI\u001b[0m\u001b[2m — \u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[36mrlm-agent\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[95mclaude-code/opus\u001b[0m\u001b[2m · \u001b[0m\u001b[2msession tutorial-14-rlm\u001b[0m \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m│\u001b[0m \u001b[2mType /help for commands. AI output may be inaccurate.\u001b[0m                  \u001b[2m│\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[96m\u001b[100m❯ Across all the files under logs/, classify every ERROR line by type (e.g. timeout, connection refused, out\r\n  of memory, permission denied) and give me a per-category count plus the noisiest file. Use your chunk → map\r\n  → reduce playbook: enumerate the files, f"]
[106.644779, "o", "an out a batched query$llm to classify, then aggregate the\r\n  structured results in a clojure fence. Inline a short chunk plan (files scanned, batches, sub-model) in your\r\n  answer.\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 1 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(27858 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(9.5s)\u001b[0m\r\n\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mIteration 1, no history. I need to enumerate the files under logs/ first, count ERROR lines, and \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2massess scale. Let me find the log files, count them, total ERROR lines, and sizes. I'll grep ERROR \u001b[0m\r\n         \u001b[2mlines so I can chunk them efficiently rather than feeding entire files. Using bash for enumeration.\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mecho \"=== File listing ===\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mfind logs -type f 2>/dev/null | sort\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mecho \"=== File count ===\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mfind logs -type f 2>/dev/null | wc -l\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mecho \"=== Per-file ERROR line counts ===\"\u001b[0m\r\n    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mfor f in $(find "]
